# YAML 1.2
# Citation File Format 1.2.0 — https://citation-file-format.github.io/
cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  OnChainAgentID: a provenance-verified benchmark for auditing
  on-chain agent-vs-human classifiers
message: >-
  If you use this benchmark or the onchain_audit toolkit, please cite
  the following work.
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Wen
    given-names: Adeline
    affiliation: University of Washington
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-15"
license: CC-BY-4.0
url: "https://github.com/adelinewen/NSF/tree/main/paper1_onchain_agent_id"
repository-code: "https://github.com/adelinewen/NSF"
keywords:
  - blockchain
  - ethereum
  - agent detection
  - benchmark
  - label leakage
  - auditing
  - machine learning
abstract: >-
  OnChainAgentID is a benchmark for agent-vs-human classification on
  Ethereum, shipping 1,147 addresses across 18 provenance-tagged
  categories, four canonical evaluation splits (random CV, temporal
  holdout, strict curated core, leave-one-platform-out), and a
  three-step Python audit toolkit (onchain_audit) for diagnosing label
  leakage in any binary classifier that consumes blockchain features.
preferred-citation:
  type: conference-paper
  title: >-
    OnChainAgentID: a provenance-verified benchmark for auditing
    on-chain agent-vs-human classifiers
  authors:
    - family-names: Wen
      given-names: Adeline
  year: 2026
  conference:
    name: "The ACM Web Conference (WWW '26)"
  collection-title: "Proceedings of the ACM Web Conference 2026"
